anity and classical culture, and the Christianization of Roman society, these letters offer a fascinating and unique view of Gregory's life, engagement with literary culture, and leadership in the church. As a single unit, this autobiographical epistolary collection proved a powerful tool in Gregory's attempts to govern the contours of his authorial image as well as his provincial and ecclesiastical legacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aRELIGION / Ancient.2bisacsh  aautobiographical epistolary collection.  aautobiography in epistolary form.  achristianity and classical culture.  achristianity.  achristianization of roman society.  aengagement with literary culture.  afascinating.  afourth century christian intelligentsia.  alate ancient letter writing.  aleadership in church.  asaint gregory of nazianzus.  aseminal figure in late antique christianity.  aunique.  aview of gregorys life.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishz978311061074108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2019z9783110606508oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520972940zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520972940423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520972940.jpg  a978-3-11-061074-1  EBOOK PACKAGE